%N A393950 Decimal expansion of (1/zeta(2))^2 * Product_{p prime} ((p/(p+2)) * Product_{k>=0} (1 + 2/p^(2^k))).
%C A393950 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is a squarefree number (A005117).
%F A393950 Equals Product_{p prime} (p+1)^2/(p*(p+2)) * A393948.
%e A393950 0.945052375049293634227126119205471990868896735111605...
%o A393950 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((p/(p+2)) * prod(k = 0, m, 1 + 2/p^(2^k)));
%o A393950 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2/zeta(2)^2}
%Y A393950 Cf. A005117, A013661, A077609, A098198, A227929.
%Y A393950 Analogous constants: A215267, A393891.
%Y A393950 The asymptotic probability that the greatest common infinitary divisor of two positive integers selected independently at random is: A065472 (square), A393948 (1), A393949 (prime), this constant (squarefree), A393951 (Fermi-Dirac prime), A393952 (exponentially 2^n-number), A393953 (4th power).
